    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Health Care in Trouble</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr David P McClary letter, commenting on June 27 article on projected budget surpluses, says now it time to upgrade national health care system, which is on brink of disaster</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>We keep hearing about anticipated federal budget surpluses (front page, June 27). And we are facing a coming disaster: failure of our present health care system.</p>
        <p>Some hospitals are going bankrupt. Some insurers can't make money in the present environment. Health care providers are being asked to deliver less care to more people. It is almost impossible for a doctor to start a new practice. Millions of citizens do not have access to health care.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>We keep hearing about anticipated federal budget surpluses (front page, June 27). And we are facing a coming disaster: failure of our present health care system.</p>
        <p>Some hospitals are going bankrupt. Some insurers can't make money in the present environment. Health care providers are being asked to deliver less care to more people. It is almost impossible for a doctor to start a new practice. Millions of citizens do not have access to health care.</p>
        <p>Now is the time for us to come together and create a national health care system for all Americans. We should take this opportunity while there is a budget surplus and before the present health care system hits rock bottom.</p>
        <p>DAVID P. MC CLARY , M.D.  New York, June 27, 2000</p>
      </block>
